[ANALYSIS]
The experiment `bow_advanced_20260421_195144_run_02` successfully executed with a BoW (Bag of Words) advanced architecture, achieving an F1 score of 0.7549 and accuracy of 0.7987. The model utilized character-level features up to 5-grams with a maximum of 18,000 features and word-level features up to 3-grams with a maximum of 25,000 features. The logistic regression parameter `C` was set to 1.0, and the validation size was 20%. 

What worked well in this experiment includes the comprehensive feature extraction strategy, which likely contributed to the relatively high accuracy and F1 score. However, there is room for improvement as the metrics could be higher, indicating potential underfitting or suboptimal hyperparameter settings.

For the next run, consider experimenting with different values of `C` in logistic regression to see if a more aggressive regularization (lower `C`) or less regularization (higher `C`) improves performance. Additionally, exploring other feature extraction techniques such as TF-IDF or word embeddings might yield better results. Adjusting the minimum document frequency (`min_df`) could also help in filtering out noise and focusing on more relevant features.